title: For Sale:  SKS M Paratrooper takes ak 47 mags 7.62x39
location: Myrtle/North Myrtle/longs, Myrtle Beach, South Carolina
postcontent:
I started on this as a project but my interests have shifted. The rifle is a norinco sks paratrooper. It came from the factory with a 16" barrel and is accepts factory ak mags. I acquired it with a cheap plastic folding stock which is included in the sale. I procured a conventional but older and now discontinued olive drab stock used by K Sports when they imported a small number of SKS's many years ago. The stock is very sturdy and tight fitting and makes a huge difference in how the rifle handles. The prior owner of the stock shortened the length of pull somewhat and refit the buttpad. The rubber pad shows signs of being refit but it is fully functional.  I replaced the rear sight with a Tech Sight adjustable model peep sight. It places the rear sight at the back cover and extends the sight radius several inches. I also replaced the front sight with a more narrow standard post for better sight picture and coupled with the rear peep sight it allows for more precise shooting than the factory sight picture. I had the muzzle threaded by a local professional smith. It is threaded 1/2-28 which is standard AR thread. Currently there is no muzzle device attached. I will include a standard AR-15 A2 flash hider which is usable on the 7.62 round.  I planned on using a muzzle brake but honestly the rifle shoots softly so it's overkill. 
    Overall the rifle is in good condition. The action is smooth and the bore is bright. I will include the original rear sight, a replacement plastic folding stock, 1 ak magazine and a ak-47 style ak cleaning kit. I don't have the cleaning rod, sorry. 

Asking price is 625.00 FTF. I will ship to an ffl if needed. I will consider trades as well. Email or text 843-798-74 eight eight.

title: For Sale:  SIG P938
postcontent: Up for sale is my sig p938 2 tone. It has exactly 170 rounds through it. I have a very good leather holster for it. Can't think of the bran name at the moment but it cost like 50 bucks. I fired 150 rounds of Remington 115 grane and a box of hornedy hallow points. It fired everything great with no problems. I purchased the sig in December so its way past the problematic ones. One thing I have to mention is that out of the whole 6 rounds my brother fired through it he had a little misshandling. He picked it up and it slipped out of his hand and landed on my shooting pad witch is the reason I have one. I said to him your lucky. We'll turns out it landed on a spent casing. It didnt put a long scratch in it, its more like a dot or a ding. He had offered to buy it off of me right there and I told him nah don't worry about it. Its not bad and its a carry piece. If it were one of my 1911's then I'd be mad but then again I hate when there's even lint on them. I feel its important to mention this because some wouldn't and would let you travel and waste gas to find out it wasn't in showroom condition as it should be with only 170 rounds through it. I think I'm making it a way bigger deal then it really it but its somthing I'd like to know. Its not a deal killer or a price dropper but I'm just letting you perfectionist like me know its there, but don't let it scare you its not bad by any means I'm just being anal about it.  I will have pictures up as soon as I whip out my camera. The ding is located on the right side rear of the pistol at the top within the cocking surrations above the extractor.   The reason I'm selling it is because it just sits in my safe and I still carry what I always carry. I'd sell it to my brother but what do ya know he went shortly after and bought one. My number is REDACTED. Thank you for reading.
